United Continental CEO Jeff Smisek Departs Amid Continuing Investigation
United Continental CEO Jeff Smisek stunned the aerospace industry on Tuesday, stepping down following a lengthy investigation involving an alleged improper relationship with the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey. WSJ's Tedd Mann joins Lunch Break With Tanya Rivero. Photo: AP
United Continental Holdings Inc. Chief Executive Jeff Smisek and two top lieutenants stepped down as the result of a federal investigation into the airline’s relationship with the former chairman of the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey.
Tuesday’s announcement by the world’s second-largest airline is a dramatic twist in the probe by prosecutors from the office of U.S. Attorney Paul Fishman, which began more than a year ago. People familiar with the investigation say it centers on whether former Port Authority Chairman...